        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(voice-call): avoid OpenAI realtime double greeting",
        "body": "Fixes #85846\n\n## Summary\n- Avoid the voice-call plugin's duplicate OpenAI realtime greeting by making the proactive greeting a single instructed `response.create` instead of injecting a synthetic user message.\n- Keep outbound OpenAI calls proactive: the bridge still calls `triggerGreeting()` on ready when an initial message exists.\n- Keep session instructions as the base voice instructions; initial greeting instructions are scoped to the first proactive response.\n- Add focused realtime handler and OpenAI provider regressions for no-message, OpenAI initial-message, non-OpenAI initial-message, and explicit speech paths.\n\n## Why\nOpenAI realtime server VAD can create a response from caller audio, while the telephony handler also needed to speak the configured outbound initial message. The previous repair disabled the proactive OpenAI greeting and moved the greeting into session instructions, which avoided duplicates but made quiet outbound calls fail to speak first. This update keeps the proactive greeting, but sends it as an instructed OpenAI response so the old duplicate synthetic-message path is avoided.\n\n## Verification\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs extensions/voice-call/src/webhook/realtime-handler.test.ts extensions/openai/realtime-voice-provider.test.ts --reporter=dot` -> 2 files, 68 tests passed\n- `./node_modules/.bin/oxfmt --check extensions/voice-call/src/webhook/realtime-handler.ts extensions/voice-call/src/webhook/realtime-handler.test.ts extensions/openai/realtime-voice-provider.ts extensions/openai/realtime-voice-provider.test.ts`\n- `./node_modules/.bin/oxlint --tsconfig config/tsconfig/oxlint.core.json extensions/voice-call/src/webhook/realtime-handler.ts extensions/voice-call/src/webhook/realtime-handler.test.ts extensions/openai/realtime-voice-provider.ts extensions/openai/realtime-voice-provider.test.ts`\n- `git diff --check refs/remotes/upstream-safe/main...HEAD`\n- `git diff --check`\n\nNote: commit `773e779eb8c76eec86a5f5bb69afdb1ae5f71f1f` is SSH-signed locally and verified with `git log --show-signature -1`. No live Twilio/OpenAI call was run in this environment.",
